sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Scheduled TaskCache Change by Uncommon Program
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Monitor the creation of a new key under 'TaskCache' when a new scheduled task is registered by a process that is not svchost.exe, which is suspicious
It is extremely abnormal for svchost.exe to spawn without any CLI arguments and is normally observed when a malicious process spawns the process and injects code into the process memory space.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Regsvr32 DLL Execution With Uncommon Extension
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects a "regsvr32" execution where the DLL doesn't contain a common file extension.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Hidden Executable In NTFS Alternate Data Stream
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the creation of an ADS (Alternate Data Stream) that contains an executable by looking at a non-empty Imphash

signature_matches.name: manipulate console buffer
signature_matches.description: host-interaction/console
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: manipulate console buffer
    namespace: host-interaction/console
    authors:
      - william.ballenthin@mandiant.com
      - michael.hunhoff@mandiant.com
    scopes:
      static: function
      dynamic: span of calls
    mbc:
      - Operating System::Console [C0033]
    references:
      - https://stackoverflow.com/a/15770935/87207
    examples:
      - 3aa7ee4d67f562933bc998f352b1f319:0x705413A0
  features:
    - or:
      - and:
        - or:
          - api: kernel32.SetConsoleCursorPosition
          - api: kernel32.ReadConsoleOutputCharacter
          - api: kernel32.WriteConsoleOutputCharacter
          - api: kernel32.WriteConsoleOutput
          - api: kernel32.WriteConsoleInput
        - optional:
          - api: kernel32.GetStdHandle
          - number: 0xfffffff5 = STD_OUTPUT_HANDLE
      - api: System.Console::Write
      - api: System.Console::WriteLine

signature_matches.name: allocate or change RWX memory
signature_matches.description: host-interaction/process/inject
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: allocate or change RWX memory
    namespace: host-interaction/process/inject
    authors:
      - "@mr-tz"
      - mehunhoff@google.com
    scopes:
      static: basic block
      dynamic: call
    mbc:
      - Memory::Allocate Memory [C0007]
    examples:
      - Practical Malware Analysis Lab 03-03.exe_:0x4010EA
      # ntdll
      - 563653399B82CD443F120ECEFF836EA3678D4CF11D9B351BB737573C2D856299:0x140001ABA
  features:
    - or:
      - basic block:
        - and:
          - or:
            - match: allocate memory
            - match: change memory protection
          - or:
            - number: 0x40 = PAGE_EXECUTE_READWRITE
            # lea     r9d, [rcx+40h]  ; flProtect
            # call    cs:VirtualAlloc
            - instruction:
              - mnemonic: lea
              - offset: 0x40 = PAGE_EXECUTE_READWRITE
      - call:
        - and:
          - or:
            - match: allocate memory
            - match: change memory protection
          - number: 0x40 = PAGE_EXECUTE_READWRITE
